Subject:
APSC invites to the lecture "Indian Constitution and Secularism"

Body:
AmbedkarPeriyar Study Circle

(An independent student body recognized by IITM)


    We welcome all to the Talk on

Indian Constitution and Secularism 


By

HonE2ble Thiru. Justice D. HariParanthaman

Retd. Judge, Madras high court



Date: 26.10.16; Venue: HSB 356; Time: 5.15 p.m



Justice D Hari Paranthaman is a retired judge of the Madras High Court.
After graduating from the Madras Law College, as a lawyer he became very
active in fighting cases in support of workers and also took part in many
democratic struggles against the corruption within the judicial system and
against casteism and communalism. During his tenure as a High court judge
from 2009 to 2016, he gave many judgments establishing the social justice
and protecting the rights of affected people including women, dalits,
loanburdened students from poor families and lowlevel workers.


